The eye-catching design ensures faster and more convenient charging for you and your family, making it an essential companion for drivers seeking a reliable and stylish solution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Impressive Performance and Innovative Design - Magtame Magnetic Coiled USB
reviews.reviewText: Magtame's Magnetic Coiled USB C to Lightning Cable is a remarkable addition to the world of charging accessories. This 3.3FT iPhone Charger Cord stands out not only for its fast-charging capabilities but also for its innovative design and MFi certification, making it a reliable choice for Apple device users.Pros:Fast Charging: The 30W power delivery ensures swift charging for your iPhones and other compatible devices. This is particularly beneficial for users who are always on the go and need a quick top-up.MFi Certified: Magtame's cable is MFi (Made for iPhone/iPad) certified, guaranteeing compatibility and reliability with Apple devices. This certification ensures that the cable meets Apple's stringent standards for quality and performance.Original Design Patent: The cable boasts an original design, indicating a commitment to innovation. The patented design sets it apart from generic cables, providing a unique and eye-catching aesthetic.Braided Cable: The braided construction of the cable enhances its durability, making it resistant to wear and tear. The added strength is especially beneficial for users who often find themselves in situations where cables undergo stress.Magnetic Coiled Feature: The magnetic coiled design is a standout feature. It not only adds a futuristic touch to the cable but also aids in cable management. The coiled structure prevents tangling and keeps the cable organized, adding to its overall convenience.USB C Compatibility: The inclusion of a USB C connector ensures versatility, allowing users to connect their devices to a wide range of power sources.Cons:Length Limitation: The cable's 3.3FT length may be limiting for users who prefer longer cables, especially in certain situations where the power source is not in close proximity.Conclusion:Magtame's Magnetic Coiled USB C to Lightning Cable is a standout product that combines fast charging capabilities with an innovative design. The MFi certification, original design patent, and durable construction make it a reliable choice for Apple device users who prioritize both performance and aesthetics. While the length may be a concern for some, the magnetic coiled feature and overall quality make this cable a worthwhile investment for those looking to upgrade their charging accessories.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Magnetic? Sure. Self-winding? Not so much.
reviews.reviewText: This charger failed to meet expectations. I would not order it again, especially at this price point. While the cord is magnetic, there’s not much reason or benefit for it—it does not self-wind like the listing states. I got this for that reason to help detangle the web of wires and chargers around my charging port. Yet, it’s just another wire for the most part.Also, the lighting cord head is too big and it’s not compatible with my phone case, which is frustrating. However, I can still use it with my AirPods.Thanks for reading my review. I hope you found it helpful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The Magtame Magnetic iPhone Charger Cord is a great option for anyone looking for a durable, tangle-free, and fast-charging cable for their iPhone. The magnetic connector is a real game-changer, and the braided cable is both stylish and practical.Pros:Magnetic connector: The magnetic connector is the best feature of this cable. It's incredibly easy to use, and it snaps into place with a satisfying click. No more fumbling around with a tiny Lightning connector!Tangle-free: The coiled design of the cable makes it tangle-free, which is a huge plus. I've never had to deal with a tangled mess of cords with this cable.Fast charging: The cable supports fast charging, so you can quickly charge your iPhone. I was able to charge my iPhone 13 Pro from 0% to 50% in about 30 minutes.Durable: The braided cable is very durable, and it's resistant to fraying and tearing. I've been using this cable for a few months now, and it shows no signs of wear and tear.MFi certified: The cable is MFi certified, which means it's been approved by Apple for use with iPhones and iPads.3.3FT length: The 3.3FT length is perfect for everyday use. It's not too long, so it won't get in the way, but it's long enough to reach comfortably from a wall outlet to your bed or couch.Cons:Price: The cable is a bit more expensive than some other options on the market. However, I think the premium features, such as the magnetic connector and the braided cable, make it worth the price.Bulky connector: The magnetic connector is a bit bulky, and it can make it difficult to use some cases. I had to remove my iPhone case in order to use the cable.Verdict:Overall, I'm very happy with the Magtame Magnetic iPhone Charger Cord. It's a well-made, durable, and fast-charging cable that makes charging my iPhone a breeze. If you're looking for a premium charging cable, I highly recommend the Magtame.Here are some additional things to consider:The cable comes in three colors: silver, black, and blue.The cable is also available in a 5FT length.Magtame offers a lifetime warranty on the cable.I hope this review helps you decide if the Magtame Magnetic iPhone Charger Cord is right for you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great cable to keep things tidy. The magnet does add a little bit of weight to it but not as much as you might expecting. For the price you’d expect a premium cable and thats sure what you’re getting here. The lightning connecter casing is on the larger side which may prove an obstruction for those with a thicker case.Testing this cable’s charging current and it does match the stated 2.4 amps current reaching 2.369 amps in my tests. Or just over 12 watts.After using this for a week, I’ve been keeping it in my work bag and the magnetic nature of this cable has kept it coiled up and refrained it from getting tangled with other cables/objects. Overall it’s a great cable but ver expensive for what you get. If this cable was 2-3meter length it would be easier to justify but at only 1 meter the amount it gets tangles is limited. If you have the funds you won’t be disappointed but each time I pull it out my bag I can’t help but think it’s not work around 4 times the cost to save me maybe a minute of untangling it from other cables.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have tons of other braided USB-C charging cables which usually require the use of cable ties to keep them neatly stored when not in use, this however is my first magnetic USB-C charging cable which does not require cable ties as the magnetic braided cord folds itself up into a compact coil.The nylon braided coil is flexible & much more durable than the rubberised silicone USB-C charging cables including the original Apple USB-C charging cables which always split, this makes this a more cost effective option than having to regularly buy endless replacements.As I own multiple devices I always keep some spare charging cables on standby to instantly replace any worn out cables when they should occur & without keeping them neatly organised they swiftly become an entangled mess which then requires time to unravel, these magnetic versions organise themselves without me having to buy additional products to keep them tidy.Neither of the USB connection ends themselves are magnetic as they are with a MacBook charging cable, only the braided cable part is actually magnetic.
